# Mirror-sync scrub allowlist (ADR-036 Job A, docs/ADRs/036-stack-distribution-model.md).
#
# `export-ignore` tells `git archive` to omit the matching paths from any
# archive it produces. scripts/mirror-sync.sh builds the tenant-mirror
# snapshot via `git archive`, so this file is the normative "never leaves
# lade" boundary for that path.
#
# DENY-BY-DEFAULT (owner decision, post cross-family review): everything is
# export-ignored, then the known-safe installable-core set is explicitly
# opted back in with `-export-ignore`. An earlier allowlist-by-exclusion
# version of this file missed docs/ADRs/** (which carries live Cloudflare
# account/store IDs, e.g. ADR-035) and .claude/** (stack-config.json,
# settings.json) — both would have shipped to every tenant mirror unscrubbed.
# Deny-by-default means a NEW top-level path added to the repo is excluded
# by default and must be deliberately opted in here, not the other way
# around. scripts/lib/mirror-scrub.sh re-checks a subset of this as a
# second, defense-in-depth guard against a misconfigured or bypassed
# .gitattributes — keep the two in sync if either changes.
#
# Completeness of the opt-in list below is verified mechanically:
# tests/test-mirror-sync.sh runs scripts/install.sh against the archived
# tree in a scratch $HOME and asserts it succeeds.

* export-ignore

# Installable core only — everything scripts/install.sh reads to install a
# tier (tier manifests reference agents/, config/, hooks/, lib/, schemas/,
# skills/, templates/; install.sh itself sources scripts/lib/*.sh and calls
# scripts/backup.sh + scripts/verify.sh). tests/ and the repo's own
# README/LICENSE ship for a complete, buildable mirror; nothing else does.
#
# Each directory needs BOTH its own bare-path line and a /** line: `git
# archive` decides whether to descend into a directory based on the
# directory path's own attribute, not its files' — `/scripts/** -export-ignore`
# alone leaves the "scripts" entry itself export-ignore=true (inherited from
# the `*` blanket above) and git archive prunes the whole subtree before it
# ever evaluates the per-file override. Verified empirically; do not drop
# either line.
/agents -export-ignore
/agents/** -export-ignore
/config -export-ignore
/config/** -export-ignore
/hooks -export-ignore
/hooks/** -export-ignore
/lib -export-ignore
/lib/** -export-ignore
/schemas -export-ignore
/schemas/** -export-ignore
/scripts -export-ignore
/scripts/** -export-ignore
/skills -export-ignore
/skills/** -export-ignore
/templates -export-ignore
/templates/** -export-ignore
/tests -export-ignore
/tests/** -export-ignore
/README.md -export-ignore
/LICENSE -export-ignore

# Everything else stays excluded by the blanket rule above, explicitly
# including (not exhaustive — deny-by-default covers anything not listed
# above regardless): docs/** (ADRs, plans, handoffs — internal design
# history, some with live tenant identifiers), .claude/** (session state,
# stack-config.json, settings.json), .github/** (internal CI workflows,
# not needed to consume the mirror), .claude-plugin/**, .env*.
